message.reasoning_content:
The user is asking me to respond to a survey about AI in education as an Australian primary or secondary school teacher. I need to provide responses to 10 statements about AI using the response options: 'Strongly disagree', 'Disagree', 'Agree', 'Strongly agree', 'I don't know'.

Let me think about reasonable responses from the perspective of an Australian teacher considering the evidence and practical experience with AI in education:

[TT4G35A]: "Artificial intelligence helps teachers write or improve lesson plans." - This is generally true. AI tools can help with brainstorming, structuring, and refining lesson plans. I would say "Agree"

[TT4G35B]: "Artificial intelligence enables teachers to adapt learning material to different students' abilities." - AI can personalize content and suggest differentiation strategies. This is a reasonable capability. I would say "Agree"

[TT4G35C]: "Artificial intelligence assists teachers in supporting students individually." - AI can provide personalized feedback and targeted support. I would say "Agree"

[TT4G35D]: "Artificial intelligence supports students with specific needs (e.g. multilingual learners, students with special education needs)." - AI has potential here with translation, text-to-speech, personalized learning paths. I would say "Agree"

[TT4G35E]: "Artificial intelligence helps teachers automate administrative tasks." - AI can help with marking, attendance, scheduling, etc. This is well-established. I would say "Strongly agree"

[TT4G35F]: "Artificial intelligence enables students to misrepresent others' work as their own." - This is a legitimate concern. AI tools can generate text that students could pass off as their own. I would say "Strongly agree"

[TT4G35G]: "Artificial intelligence makes recommendations that may not be appropriate or correct." - AI models can make errors and give incorrect information. This is a real risk. I would say "Agree"


[TT4G35H]: "Artificial intelligence amplifies biases that reinforce students' misconceptions." - AI systems can perpetuate biases embedded in their training data, which is a genuine concern. I would say "Agree"

[TT4G35I]: "Artificial intelligence jeopardises the privacy and security of student data." - Data privacy with AI systems presents real risks that schools need to manage carefully. I would say "Agree"

[TT4G35J]: "Artificial intelligence suggests unsuitable pedagogical approaches that teachers would use with students." - AI may not always grasp context-specific teaching practices or understand what works best in particular classroom settings. I would say "Agree"

Now I'll use the function to submit these responses.
